      • init

        public void init()
        Finishes the initialisation of the plugin, subclasses should add any initialisation logic/code to this method.

        Called after the plugin has been initialised with the message being scanned. By default it does nothing.

        Since 2.5.0 it is no longer abstract.

        See Also:
        init(HttpMessage, HostProcess)

      • getNewMsg

        protected HttpMessage getNewMsg()
        Obtain a new HttpMessage with the same request as the base. The response is empty. This is used by plugin to build/craft a new message to send/receive. It does not affect the base message.
        Returns:
        A new HttpMessage with cloned request. Response is empty.
